NanoTrasen isn't just a company, it is The Company. The largest corporation (at least according to themselves) ever to exist, NanoTrasen is on the cutting edge of just about every scientific field, due in large part to their focus on research of alien artifacts and strange spacetime anomalies. However, being top dog is a precarious position, and NanoTrasen finds itself a constant target of [[Syndicate|saboteurs]], both overt and subtle.

Fortunately, the Cosmatic Sector is so far out in deep space, and its research so vague and preliminary, that it is largely insulated from the corporate warfare that plagues much of NanoTrasen-controlled space.

== History ==

Originally founded by [NAME] NanoTrasen begun in [DATE] as a small Sol-bound tech start up with a focus on circuit engineering and a small handful of employees. NT would continue on this course for several years as they slowly grew in size before broadening their scope to plasma research after it was discovered, spending a good portion of their funds on a highly experimental space station to conduct said research. NT's venture into plasma research was extremely successful, becoming a key player in the field and attracting a lot more attention to themselves as a potentially promising company. Eventually NT started getting contracted for infrastructure and military research and development by the Sol Government. Leveraging the Government's funding and their requests, NT was able to justify more and even larger expansions of their company; starting work on several new stations and planetary facilities across multiple Sol adjacent sectors.

Being seen as quite reliable by the Sol Government, they kept contracting NanoTrasen and they quickly became a staple in Sol's research and development. During this period NT was given plenty of resources and time to continue their growth and start extending their hands into as many notable corners of the intergalactic market as possible. If NT saw potential profit to be made, they jumped on the opportunity; household chemicals, energy solutions, space ship construction, advanced robotics, military hardware, the list goes on. NanoTrasen had enough income from their plasma products alone to become a mega corporation, it's no surprise they became simply too big to be competed with properly, but then The Syndicate was formed. With a focus to tear down every mega corporation they could, The Syndicate's prime target from the start was NT.